# Privacy Policy for PinSmart Extension

*Last Updated: March 22, 2025*

## Introduction

Thank you for choosing PinSmart ("we", "us", or "our"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our PinSmart browser extension. We are committed to protecting your privacy and handling your data with transparency and care.

Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. By installing, accessing, or using PinSmart, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with the terms of this Privacy Policy, please do not install or use the extension.

## Information We Collect

### Information You Provide to Us

- **Pinterest Account Information**: When you connect your Pinterest account, we request access to your Pinterest boards and profile information to enable core extension functionality.
- **User Preferences**: Settings and preferences you configure within the extension.

### Information We Collect Automatically

- **Image Data**: When you select an image to pin, we process the image URL and metadata.
- **Usage Data**: Information about how you interact with the extension, such as features used and actions taken.
- **Technical Data**: Technical information such as your browser type and version, and the type of device you use.

### Image Analysis

PinSmart analyzes images you select to provide smart categorization and tagging suggestions. This analysis occurs locally within the extension and through secure API calls. The image content is processed to identify objects, themes, and relevant categories, but is not permanently stored by us beyond what is necessary to provide the service.

## How We Use Your Information

We use the information we collect to:

- Provide and maintain the PinSmart extension
- Suggest appropriate Pinterest boards and tags based on image content
- Identify potential affiliate marketing opportunities related to image content
- Improve and optimize the extension's functionality
- Detect and address technical issues
- Protect against misuse or unauthorized use of our extension

## Data Sharing and Disclosure

### Third-Party Services

PinSmart integrates with the following third-party services:

- **Pinterest API**: To enable core pinning functionality
- **Google Cloud Vision API** (or similar image analysis service): For analyzing image content to suggest categorizations
- **Affiliate Networks**: To identify potential affiliate opportunities

These third-party services have their own privacy policies that govern how they use your data. We encourage you to review their privacy policies.

### Legal Requirements

We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities (e.g., a court or government agency).

## Data Security

We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect the security of your personal information. However, please be aware that no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure.

## Data Retention

We retain your information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, and as required by law. When we no longer need your data, we will securely delete or anonymize it.

## Your Rights

Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal information, including:

- The right to access personal information we hold about you
- The right to request correction of inaccurate data
- The right to request deletion of your data
- The right to restrict or object to our processing of your data
- The right to data portability

To exercise these rights, please contact us using the information provided at the end of this policy.

## Children's Privacy

Our extension is not intended for use by children under the age of 16. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 16. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us.

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

## Third-Party Links and Services

PinSmart may contain links to other websites or services that are not operated by us. If you click on a third-party link, you will be directed to that third party's site. We strongly advise you to review the Privacy Policy of every site you visit. We have no control over and assume no responsibility for the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party sites or services.

## Affiliate Marketing Disclosure

PinSmart includes features that identify potential affiliate marketing opportunities in images. When you use these features:

- We analyze image content to identify products or services
- We may suggest affiliate programs or retailers related to the identified content
- If you choose to pursue these opportunities, you may be directed to third-party affiliate platforms

Please note that any transactions or relationships you establish with these third-party affiliate programs are governed by their respective terms and privacy policies.

## Cookie Policy

PinSmart uses local storage and browser cookies to store your preferences and settings. These technologies help us recognize you when you use the extension and provide a more personalized experience.

## Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:

- Email: wushumaster75@gmail.com

## California Privacy Rights

If you are a California resident, you have specific rights regarding your personal information under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA). This includes the right to request disclosure of information we collect and share about you, and the right to request deletion of your data. To make such requests, please contact us using the information provided above.

## International Data Transfers

Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than the country in which you reside. These countries may have data protection laws that are different from the laws of your country. By using PinSmart, you consent to this transfer, storing, and processing.

